menu "breadboard: bb_diag"

config BB_DIAG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    bool "Capture log tail to RTC RAM for panic diagnosis"
    default y
    help
        Mirrors bb_log_stream output to RTC slow memory so the last
        few KB of log lines survive a software reboot. Exposed via
        GET /api/diag/panic on the next boot if the previous boot was
        abnormal (panic, watchdog, brownout). Costs CONFIG_BB_DIAG_PANIC_BUF_SIZE
        bytes of RTC slow memory.

config BB_DIAG_PANIC_BUF_SIZE
    int "Panic log RTC buffer size (bytes)"
    default 2048
    range 512 8192
    depends on BB_DIAG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    help
        Size of the circular buffer in RTC slow memory. Must fit in
        the chip's RTC slow memory budget (~8KB on ESP32-S3, less on
        smaller chips). 2 KB captures roughly the last 30-50 log lines.

config BB_DIAG_PANIC_COREDUMP
    bool "Capture ESP-IDF coredump for panic backtraces"
    default n
    depends on BB_DIAG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    help
        On panic, ESP-IDF writes a coredump to a dedicated flash partition.
        On the next boot, bb_diag_panic decodes it via esp_core_dump_get_summary
        and exposes the task name, exception PC, and backtrace via
        GET /api/diag/panic. Requires a "coredump" partition entry in the
        consumer's partitions.csv (see examples/smoke/partitions.*.csv for
        the 64 KB layout). Also requires the following in sdkconfig.defaults:
            CONFIG_ESP_COREDUMP_ENABLE_TO_FLASH=y
            CONFIG_ESP_COREDUMP_DATA_FORMAT_ELF=y
            CONFIG_ESP_COREDUMP_CHECKSUM_CRC32=y
        Disabled by default to avoid forcing the partition change on existing
        consumers.

config BB_DIAG_ROUTES
    bool "Build bb_diag HTTP routes (/api/diag/panic GET+DELETE) and /api/info extender"
    default y
    depends on BB_DIAG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag registers GET/DELETE /api/diag/panic and
        adds an optional "panic" block to /api/info via
        bb_info_register_extender. Adds bb_http, bb_json, bb_registry,
        and bb_info to bb_diag's PRIV_REQUIRES.

config BB_DIAG_PANIC_TRIGGER
    bool "Expose POST /api/diag/panic/trigger to force a panic (debug only)"
    default n
    depends on BB_DIAG_ROUTES
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag exposes POST /api/diag/panic/trigger which
        deliberately dereferences a null pointer to force a LoadProhibited
        panic. Used to validate panic capture / coredump end-to-end on bench
        hardware without physically rebooting the device. NEVER ship to
        production: any unauthenticated caller can crash the firmware.

config BB_DIAG_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-init bb_diag panic capture + routes via bb_registry"
    default y
    depends on BB_DIAG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag_panic_init runs in the early registry tier
        (before HTTP server start) to detect prior-boot panic state and
        install the log-stream tap, and bb_diag_routes_init runs in the
        regular tier to register HTTP routes and the info extender.

endmenu
